The independent review into the Ashwin Willemse walk-out has found that the conduct of Nick Mallett and Naas Botha “does not manifest naked racism”. The former Springbok rugby wing walked off of the SuperSport set in May after he had accused co-hosts Nick Mallett and Naas Botha of patronising him. An independent review was conducted by advocate Vincent Maleka with the assistance of Wits University’s Professor Adam Habib. Read the full report below: 